==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sheathbill
<hw>Sheath"bill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Either one of two species of birds composing the genus
<gen>Chionis</gen>, and family <fam>Chionidae</fam>, native of the
islands of the Antarctic seas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ They are related to the gulls and the plovers, but more
nearly to the latter. The base of the bill is covered with a
saddle-shaped horny sheath, and the toes are only slightly webbed. The
plumage of both species is white.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sheathe</ent>⟦br⟧
